1- Do you find the code to be simpler when using AngularJS? If so, how? If not, why?
It is a more elegant solution but we needed to learn AngularJS and get accustomed to it.

2- Would a beginner to front-end development find the code to be simpler? Why or why not?
Yes because we don't need to directly manipulate the DOM and to learn the javascripts method that are needed to update the DOM.

3- How might the structure provided by AngularJS simplify building larger web applications?
Because it provides a more elegant solution, it will be much simpler to build larger applications, it includes less typing and removes a lot of redundancy since the controllers and their methods can be reused in different parts of the app.
